  "prompt": "What should I put on sweet potato fries?",
  "response": "Sweet potato fries can be enhanced with a variety of toppings and dips! Here are some delicious ideas to consider:\n\n### Dipping Sauces:\n1. **Honey Mustard**: A sweet and tangy complement.\n2. **Garlic Aioli**: Creamy and flavorful.\n3. **Chipotle Mayo**: Adds a smoky kick.\n4. **Ranch Dressing**: A classic choice for dipping.\n5. **Sriracha or Hot Sauce**: For a spicy kick.\n6. **Balsamic Glaze**: Sweet and tangy with a touch of sophistication.\n\n### Seasonings and Toppings:\n1. **Sea Salt and Pepper**: Simple yet effective.\n2. **Cinnamon and Sugar**: For a sweet twist.\n3. **Parmesan Cheese**: Adds a savory and salty depth.\n4. **Chili Powder or Paprika**: For a smoky and spicy flavor.\n5. **Fresh Herbs**: Like parsley, cilantro, or rosemary for freshness.\n\n### Other Ideas:\n1. **Avocado or Guacamole**: Creamy and delicious.\n2. **Feta Cheese**: Crumbled, for a tangy touch.\n3. **Chopped Green Onions**: Adds a bit of sharpness and color.\n4. **Pico de Gallo**: For a fresh and zesty topping.\n5. **Cilantro Lime Crema**: A refreshing sauce to drizzle on top.\n\nFeel free to mix and match these ideas to find your perfect combination!",
